CHECK_DESCRIPTION: Count of records per person per month.
A yes or no value indicating if all fields are present in the @CDM_TABLE table as expected based on the specification.
The number and percent of records with a NULL value in the @CDM_FIELD of the @CDM_TABLE that is considered not nullable.
A yes or no value indicating if the @CDM_FIELD in the @CDM_TABLE is the expected data type based on the specification.
The number and percent of records that have a duplicate value in the @CDM_FIELD field of the @CDM_TABLE.
The number and percent of records that have a value in the @CDM_FIELD field in the @CDM_TABLE table that does not exist in the @FK_TABLE table.
The number and percent of records that have a value in the @CDM_FIELD field in the @CDM_TABLE table that do not conform to the @FK_DOMAIN domain.
The number and percent of records that have a value in the @CDM_FIELD field in the @CDM_TABLE table that do not conform to the @FK_CLASS class.
The number and percent of records that do not have a standard, valid concept in the @CDM_FIELD field in the @CDM_TABLE table.
The number and percent of records with a NULL value in the @CDM_FIELD of the @CDM_TABLE.
The number and percent of records with a value of 0 in the standard concept field @CDM_FIELD in the @CDM_TABLE table.
The number and percent of records with a value of 0 in the source concept field @CDM_FIELD in the @CDM_TABLE table.
The number and percent of distinct source values in the @CDM_FIELD field of the @CDM_TABLE table mapped to 0.
The number and percent of records with a value in the @CDM_FIELD field of the @CDM_TABLE table less than @PLAUSIBLE_VALUE_LOW.
The number and percent of records with a value in the @CDM_FIELD field of the @CDM_TABLE table greater than @PLAUSIBLE_VALUE_HIGH.

The number and percent of records with a value in the @CDM_FIELD field of the @CDM_TABLE that occurs prior to the date in the @PLAUSIBLE_TEMPORAL_AFTER field of the @PLAUSIBLE_TEMPORAL_AFTER_TABLE table.
If yes, the number and percent of records with a date value in the @CDM_FIELD field of the @CDM_TABLE table that occurs after death.

For the combination of CONCEPT_ID @CONCEPT_ID (@CONCEPT_NAME) and UNIT_CONCEPT_ID @UNIT_CONCEPT_ID (@UNIT_CONCEPT_NAME), the number and percent of records that have a value less than @PLAUSIBLE_VALUE_LOW.

For the combination of CONCEPT_ID @CONCEPT_ID (@CONCEPT_NAME) and UNIT_CONCEPT_ID @UNIT_CONCEPT_ID (@UNIT_CONCEPT_NAME), the number and percent of records that have a value less than @PLAUSIBLE_VALUE_HIGH.
For a CONCEPT_ID @CONCEPT_ID (@CONCEPT_NAME), the number and percent of records associated with patients with an implausible gender (@PLAUSIBLE_GENDER).
